<ns4952:section xmlns:ns4952="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.platforms.linux.sed.scriptFiles">

  <ns4953:title xmlns:ns4953="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Using script files</ns4953:title>
  <ns4954:para xmlns:ns4954="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    For more elaborate transformations (for example when transformin a complete
    <ns4955:emphasis xmlns:ns4955="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">LaTeX</ns4955:emphasis> document into a <ns4956:emphasis xmlns:ns4956="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">docbook</ns4956:emphasis>
    document), one would have a large number of transformations which need to
    be applied across a document.
  </ns4954:para>
  <ns4957:para xmlns:ns4957="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    Sed script files may contain comments which start with a hash, <ns4958:literal xmlns:ns4958="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">#</ns4958:literal>.
    Each line in the script file contains a transformation rule.
  </ns4957:para>
</ns4952:section>